<strong>opportunity:</strong><br>\r\n                                                poverty<br>\r\n                                                employment<br>\r\n                                                community_basics<br>\r\n                                                entrepreneurship<br>\r\n                                                <strong>health_and_environment:</strong><br>\r\n                                                physical_health<br>\r\n                                                mental_health<br>\r\n                                                environmental_health<br>\r\n                                                <strong>freedom:</strong><br>\r\n                                                political_freedom<br>\r\n                                                civil_liberties<br>\r\n                                                religious_freedom<br>\r\n                                                economic_freedom<br>\r\n                                                perceived_freedom<br>\r\n                                                <strong>community_and_relationships:</strong><br>\r\n                                                community_life<br>\r\n                                                family_life<br>\r\n                                                <strong>living_standard:</strong><br>\r\n                                                current_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                improvement_in_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                <strong>peace_and_security:</strong><br>\r\n                                                violence_and_ethnic_warfare<br>\r\n                                                human_rights_violations<br>\r\n                                                law_and_order<br>\r\n                                                trust_in_national_institutions<br>\r\n                                                corruption_in_business_and_government<br>\r\n                                                bureaucracy_quality\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <p></p>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <p></p>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                             <tr>\r\n                                <td>sub-components</td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    Returns the data for the individual subcomponents passed in on the request. Also compares the scores of the returned subcomponents and ranks the states accordingly.<p></p>\r\n                                    <p>Subcomponents are passed in as a pipe-delimited list of the subcomponents name.</p>\r\n                                    <h4>Example</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey&amp;subcomponents=poverty_rate|unemployment_rate|employment_growth</p>\r\n                                    <div class="row">\r\n                                        <div class="large-12 medium-12 columns">\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-link">\r\n                                            <a href="#">Available U.S. Subcomponents \r\n                                                <i class="fi-arrow-down"></i>\r\n                                                <i class="fi-arrow-up"></i></a>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-list">\r\n                                                <strong>poverty:</strong><br>\r\n                                                poverty_rate<br>\r\n                                                income_of_the_bottom_25<br>\r\n                                                <strong>employment:</strong><br>\r\n                                                unemployment_rate<br>\r\n                                                long_term_unemployment_rate<br>\r\n                                                labor_participation_rate<br>\r\n                                                <strong>community_vitality:</strong><br>\r\n                                                perceived_community_improvement<br>\r\n                                                employment_growth<br>\r\n                                                percent_increase_in_businesses<br>\r\n                                                <strong>education:</strong><br>\r\n                                                8th_grade_test_scores<br>\r\n                                                high_school_dropout_rate<br>\r\n                                                <strong>physical_health:</strong><br>\r\n                                                male_life_expectancy<br>\r\n                                                female_life_expectancy<br>\r\n                                                obesity_rate<br>\r\n                                                <strong>mental_health:</strong><br>\r\n                                                suicide_rate<br>\r\n                                                prevalence_of_worrying<br>\r\n                                                prevalence_of_anger<br>\r\n                                                <strong>environmental_health:</strong><br>\r\n                                                satisfaction_with_location<br>\r\n                                                access_to_safe_water<br>\r\n                                                access_to_fruits_and_vegetables<br>\r\n                                                access_to_medicine<br>\r\n                                                access_to_a_safe_place_to_exercise<br>\r\n                                                <strong>community_life:</strong><br>\r\n                                                volunteer_rate<br>\r\n                                                religious_engagement<br>\r\n                                                <strong>family_life:</strong><br>\r\n                                                prevalence_of_marriage<br>\r\n                                                prevalence_of_divorce<br>\r\n                                                children_in_single_parent_families<br>\r\n                                                time_spent_with_friends_and_family<br>\r\n                                                <strong>current_living_standard:</strong><br>\r\n                                                personal_income_per_capita<br>\r\n                                                perceived_current_standard_of_living<br>\r\n                                                <strong>improvement_in_living_standard:</strong><br>\r\n                                                personal_income_per_capita_growth<br>\r\n                                                perceived_improvement_in_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                <strong>education:</strong><br>\r\n                                                choice\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <p></p>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div class="large-12 medium-12 columns">\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-link">\r\n                                                <a href="#">Available World Subcomponents \r\n                                                    <i class="fi-arrow-down"></i>\r\n                                                    <i class="fi-arrow-up"></i></a>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-list">\r\n                                                <strong>poverty:</strong><br>\r\n                                                poverty_rate<br>\r\n                                                income_of_bottom_20<br>\r\n                                                <strong>employment:</strong><br>\r\n                                                unemployment_rate<br>\r\n                                                labor_participation_rate<br>\r\n                                                perceived_job_availability<br>\r\n                                                <strong>community_vitality:</strong><br>\r\n                                                access_to_basic_needs<br>\r\n                                                communications_infrastructure<br>\r\n                                                <strong>entrepreneurship:</strong><br>\r\n                                                business_startup_costs<br>\r\n                                                time_to_start_a_business<br>\r\n                                                perceived_climate_for_new_businesses<br>\r\n                                                <strong>physical_health:</strong><br>\r\n                                                life_expectancy_at_birth<br>\r\n                                                life_expectancy_at_age_60<br>\r\n                                                infant_mortality_rate<br>\r\n                                                undernourishment<br>\r\n                                                <strong>mental_and_emotional_health:</strong><br>\r\n                                                suicide_rate<br>\r\n                                                positive_experience<br>\r\n                                                suffering<br>\r\n                                                <strong>environmental_health:</strong><br>\r\n                                                air_quality<br>\r\n                                                water_quality<br>\r\n                                                sanitation<br>\r\n                                                <strong>political_freedom:</strong><br>\r\n                                                political_rights<br>\r\n                                                expression_of_political_views_without_fear<br>\r\n                                                <strong>community_life:</strong><br>\r\n                                                civic_engagement<br>\r\n                                                religious_engagement<br>\r\n                                                <strong>family_life:</strong><br>\r\n                                                prevalence_of_marriage<br>\r\n                                                prevalence_of_divorce<br>\r\n                                                time_spent_with_friends_and_family<br>\r\n                                                <strong>current_living_standard:</strong><br>\r\n                                                gdp_per_capita<br>\r\n                                                perceived_current_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                <strong>improvement_in_living_standard:</strong><br>\r\n                                                gdp_per_capita_growth<br>\r\n                                                perceived_improvement_in_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                <strong>community_vitality:</strong><br>\r\n                                                literacy_rate<br>\r\n                                                <strong>family_life:</strong><br>\r\n                                                children_living_with_biological_parents\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <p></p>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <p></p>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                sub-sub-components\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    Returns the data for the individual sub-subcomponents passed in on the request. Also compares the scores of the returned sub-sub-components and ranks the states accordingly.<p></p>\r\n                                    <p>Sub-subcomponents are passed in as a pipe-delimited list of the sub-subcomponents name.</p>\r\n                                    <h4>Example</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey&amp;sub-sub-subcomponents=reading|math|science</p>\r\n                                    <div class="row">\r\n                                        <div class="large-12 medium-12 columns">\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-link">\r\n                                                <a href="#">Available U.S. Sub-subcomponents \r\n                                                <i class="fi-arrow-down"></i>\r\n                                                <i class="fi-arrow-up"></i></a>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-list">\r\n                                                <strong>8th_grade_test_scores:</strong><br>\r\n                                                reading<br>\r\n                                                math<br>\r\n                                                science<br>\r\n                                                <strong>high_school_dropout_rate:</strong><br>\r\n                                                prevalence_of_charter_schools<br>\r\n                                                educational_freedom<br>\r\n                                                <strong>religious_engagement:</strong><br>\r\n                                                importance_of_religion<br>\r\n                                                religious_attendance<br>\r\n                                                <strong>perceived_improvement_in_living_standard:</strong><br>\r\n                                                perceived_improvement_in_personal_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                perceived_improvement_in_personal_financial_situation\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <p></p>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div class="large-12 medium-12 columns">\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-link">\r\n                                                <a href="#">Available World Sub-subcomponents \r\n                                                    <i class="fi-arrow-down"></i><i class="fi-arrow-up"></i>\r\n                                                </a>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-list">\r\n                                                <strong>communications_infrastructure:</strong><br>\r\n                                                mobile_phone_subscriptions<br>\r\n                                                broadband_internet_subscriptions<br>\r\n                                                <strong>perceived_current_living_standard:</strong><br>\r\n                                                perceived_personal_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                perceived_national_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                <strong>perceived_improvement_in_living_standard:</strong><br>\r\n                                                perceived_improvement_in_personal_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                perceived_improvement_in_national_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                <strong>religious_engagement:</strong><br>\r\n                                                importance_of_religion<br>\r\n                                                religious_attendance<br>\r\n                                                <strong>prevalence_of_marriage:</strong><br>\r\n                                                marriage_rate<br>\r\n                                                self_reported_marriage<br>\r\n                                                <strong>prevalence_of_divorce:</strong><br>\r\n                                                divorce_rate<br>\r\n                                                self_reported_divorce\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <p></p>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <p></p>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                        </tbody>\r\n                    </table>\r\n                    <p>These Parameters can be combined to increase the specificity of your search. For example:</p>\r\n                    <p>http://life-measures.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey&amp;locations=va|md|pa&amp;years=2002|2003|2004&amp;dimensions=opportunity|health_and_environment|freedom</p>\r\n                    <p>or</p>\r\n                    <p>http://life-measures.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey&amp;locations=af|al|dz&amp;years=2002|2003|2004&amp;dimensions=opportunity|health_and_environment|freedom</p>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n    </div>', 'Quality of Life', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-03 17:35:50', '2015-03-03 17:35:50', '', 4, 'http://localhost/life-measures-wordpress/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
	(104, 1, '2015-03-03 17:38:58', '2015-03-03 17:38:58', '<section class="intro-image" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.staging-putty.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/cki-template11-headers-api.jpg\');">\r\n        <header>\r\n                            <h1>How to Use Our Data API</h1>\r\n                <hr/>\r\n                    </header>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Introduction</h2>\r\n                    <hr/>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <p>Before you can access the API data, you will first need to get a registration key that you will need to use on all of your requests. <a href="/get-the-data/api-registration/">Click here</a> to get your registration key.</p>\r\n<p>To gain access to raw information regarding the locations, dimensions, components, and scores affiliated with each Index (U.S. Index or World Index), please use one of the following URL use cases.</p>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Resources</h2>\r\n                    <hr/>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>\r\n            Resources\r\n        </th>\r\n<th>\r\n            Description\r\n        </th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/locations/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/locations/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<strong>Locations</strong><br />\r\n            Returns a list of all states or nations included in the Well-Being Initiative’s Index.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/dimensionlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/dimensionlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<strong>Dimensions</strong><br />\r\n            Returns a list of the dimensions of well-being, which are shared by the U.S. and World Indices.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/componentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/componentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><strong>Components</strong><br />\r\n            Returns a list of all components (and their parent dimensions) included in the U.S. and World Indices.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/subcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/subcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><strong>Sub-Components</strong><br />\r\n            Returns a list of all sub-components (and their parent components) included in the U.S. and World Indices.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/subsubcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/subsubcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><strong>Sub-Sub-Components</strong><br />\r\n            Returns a list of all sub-sub-components (and their parent sub-components) included in the U.S. and World Indices.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Scores</h2>\r\n                    <hr/>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Scores</th>\r\n<th>Description</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/summary/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/summary/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>Summary Scores</strong><br />\r\nReturns all states or nations, scores and rankings related with the Well-Being Initiative’s Index for the most recent year that we have data.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>All Scores</strong><br />\r\nReturns all states or nations, dimensions, components, subcomponents, sub-sub-components, scores and rankings related with the Well-Being Initiative’s Index. Includes historical data back to 2001 for US data, and 2000 for World data.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/dimensions/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/dimensions/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>Dimension Scores</strong><br />\r\nReturns all dimension scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Index.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/components/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/components/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>Component Scores</strong>Returns all component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Index.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/subcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/subcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>Sub-Component Scores</strong><br />\r\nReturns all sub-component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Index.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/subsubcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/subsubcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>Sub-Sub-Component Scores</strong><br />\r\nReturns all sub-sub-component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Index.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Targeted Queries</h2>\r\n                    <hr/>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <p>Generating targeted lists of specific data points is done by adding query parameters to your URL. This can allow you to specify your search criteria (ex.; locations, years, dimensions, components, etc.) and get a detailed object of that data as well as a calculated score and ranking based on the returned data.</p>\r\n<h3>Base URLs</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n            U.S.\r\n        </td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<p>            This call will return all states, dimensions, components, subcomponents, sub-sub-components, and all of the scores related to the Well-Being Initiative’s U.S. Index. Includes historical data back to 2001.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n            World\r\n        </td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<p>            This call will return all countries, dimensions, components, subcomponents, sub-sub-components, and all of the scores related to the Well-Being Initiative’s World Index. Includes historical data back to 2000.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>Parameters</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n            locations\r\n        </td>\r\n<td>\r\n            Returns all of the data for the individual states passed in on the request. Also compares the scores of the returned states and ranks them accordingly.</p>\r\n<p>            States and countries are passed in as a pipe-delimited list of the two-letter state/country abbreviations.</p>\r\n<h4>Example</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey&#038;locations=ca|ny|va</p>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="large-6 medium-6 columns">\r\n<div class="parameter-link"><a href="#">Available U.S. Locations <i class="fi-arrow-down"></i><i class="fi-arrow-up"></i></a></div>\r\n<div class="parameter-list">\r\n                        AL &rarr; Alabama<br />\r\n                        AK &rarr; Alaska<br />\r\n                        AZ &rarr; Arizona<br />\r\n                        AR &rarr; Arkansas<br />\r\n                        CA &rarr; California<br />\r\n                        CO &rarr; Colorado<br />\r\n                        CT &rarr; Connecticut<br />\r\n                        DE &rarr; Delaware<br />\r\n                        FL &rarr; Florida<br />\r\n                        GA &rarr; Georgia<br />\r\n                        HI &rarr; Hawaii<br />\r\n                        ID &rarr; Idaho<br />\r\n                        IL &rarr; Illinois<br />\r\n               