div class="dimension large-4 medium-6 small-12 columns opportunity">\r\n                            <h3>Opportunity</h3>\r\n                            <p>Categories:</p>\r\n                            <p>Poverty<br />\r\n                                Employment<br />\r\n                                Community Basics<br />\r\n                                Entrepreneurship</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class="dimension large-4 medium-6 small-12 columns health_and_environment">\r\n                            <h3>Health &#038; Environment</h3>\r\n                            <br>\r\n                            <p>Categories:</p>\r\n                            <p>Physical Health<br />\r\n                                Mental Health<br />\r\n                                Environmental Health</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class="dimension large-4 medium-6 small-12 columns freedom">\r\n                            <h3>Freedom</h3>\r\n                            <br>\r\n                            <p>Categories:</p>\r\n                            <p>Political Freedom<br />\r\n                                Civil Liberties<br />\r\n                                Religious Freedom<br />\r\n                                Economic Freedom<br />\r\n                                Perceived Freedom</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class="dimension large-4 medium-6 small-12 columns community_and_relationships">\r\n                            <h3>Community &#038; Relationships</h3>\r\n                            <br>\r\n                            <p>Categories:</p>\r\n                            <p>Community Life<br />\r\n                                Family Life</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class="dimension large-4 medium-6 small-12 columns living_standard">\r\n                            <h3>Living Standard</h3>\r\n                            <br>\r\n                            <p>Categories:</p>\r\n                            <p>Current Living Standard<br />\r\n                                Improvement in Living Standard</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class="dimension large-4 medium-6 small-12 columns peace_and_security">\r\n                            <h3>Peace &#038; Security</h3>\r\n                            <br>\r\n                            <p>Categories:</p>\r\n                            <p>Violence and Ethnic Warfare<br />\r\n                                Human Rights Violations<br />\r\n                                Corruption in Business & Government<br />\r\n                                Trust in National Institutions<br />\r\n                                Law and Order<br />\r\n                                Bureaucracy Quality</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n                <p>Learn more about the sources of these measurements.”</p>\r\n                <a class="btn flat gray download pdf variables" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/pdf/Quality_of_Life_Variables_US_Measures.pdf" target="_blank">Download U.S. Variables</a>\r\n\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n            <div class="row">\r\n                <a name="glossary"></a>\r\n                <section class="glossary">\r\n                    <header class="title-group">\r\n                    <h2>Glossary</h2>\r\n                    <hr>\r\n                    </header>\r\n                    <div class="row">\r\n                        <div class="glossary-item-container large-12 medium-12 small-12 columns">\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Component</h3>\r\n                                <p>The different qualities of a particular dimension. For example, the components of the freedom dimension are civil liberties, economic freedom, political freedom, religious freedom, and perception of freedom.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Component Score</h3>\r\n                                <p>The value obtained from averaging the scores for subcomponents within a particular component for a country or U.S. state.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Dimension</h3>\r\n                                <p>One of the six key elements of Quality of Life Measures(i.e., Living Standard, Health &amp; Environment, Freedom, Opportunity, Community &amp; Relationships, or Peace &amp; Security) as defined by the Measures of Quality of Life.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Dimension Score</h3>\r\n                                <p>The value obtained from averaging the scores for components within a particular dimension for a country or U.S. state.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Happiness</h3>\r\n                                <p>The range of positive feelings, stretching from contentment to joy, that a person experiences.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Life Satisfaction</h3>\r\n                                <p>A person’s cognitive, evaluative reflection of that individual’s life as a whole.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Life ability</h3>\r\n                                <p>A measurement of an individual’s internal capacity to be happy and satisfied and his or her adeptness at taking advantage of the external environment.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Livability</h3>\r\n                                <p>A measurement of how the external, societal environment enables Quality of Life Measures.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Normalization</h3>\r\n                                <p>The method used to reconcile variables that are based on different units of measurement.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Objective Variables</h3>\r\n                                <p>Quantifiable social or economic variables that are based on specific standards and reported by outside observers.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Score</h3>\r\n                                <p>The normalized value used to estimate each variable. The variable scores are aggregated for subcomponents, components, and dimensions and result in the final measurement of the Quality of Life of a country or U.S. state.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Subcomponent</h3>\r\n                                <p>One of two or more factors of a component. For example, the Living Standard dimension consists of the two components of current living standard and improvement in living standard. The improvement in living standard component includes the 5-year growth in GDP and perceptions of improvement in living standard as subcomponents.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Subcomponent Score</h3>\r\n                                <p>The value obtained from averaging the scores for variables within a particular subcomponent for a country or U.S. state.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Subjective Variables</h3>\r\n                                <p>Variables that are individually perceived and obtained through self-reported methods.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Variable</h3>\r\n                                <p>One of many attributes used to characterize a certain aspect of the Quality of Life Measures of a country or U.S. state. There are 50 variables in the World measurements and 42 in the U.S. measurements.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Variable Score</h3>\r\n                                <p>The normalized value used to estimate each attribute of the Quality of Life Measures of a country or U.S. state.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="glossary-item">\r\n                                <h3>Quality of Life Measures Score</h3>\r\n                                <p>The value obtained from averaging the six dimension scores for a country or U.S. state.<br>\r\n                                Quality of Life Measures consists of the two underlying concepts of happiness and life satisfaction and emanates both from societal factors (livability) and from the internal personal dynamics that enable the individual to benefit from the societal environment (life ability).</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </section>\r\n            </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n', 'Quality of Life Measures', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '224-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-07 07:34:33', '2015-03-07 07:34:33', '', 224, 'http://localhost/life-measures-wordpress/224-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
